										introduce the participants followed by a message from Ms. Lala
										Munzones in behalf of Dr. Annabee Magbanua-Claur the Dean of
										the College of Arts and Sciences.</p>
									<p>Introduction of speaker by Dr. Corazon G. Acaba. Our
										speaker started by introducing himself, telling us about his
										background. He ask the participants about their expectation of
										the seminar. After, he begin the lecture with a business
										foundation topic. Discussing the difference between business
										models and business plan. Choosing the right business model
										and business plan for your business.</p>
									<p>Mr. Nisperos started the afternoon session with a game.
										A game where each group of participants needs to present their
										idea about enhancing the wallet of one of the participant and
										try to convince her to buy their product afterwards. Everyone
										made their own version of wallet without knowing it's not just
										a usual game. Mr. Nisperos revealed the twist of the game. He
										told everyone that before creating something you just need to
										know what the client wants. Where no one else did during the
										game. 2 groups won the prize which is a book co-authored by
										Mr. Nisperos entitled "CYBERPRENEUR". After the game, he
										explained the factors that need to be consider while doing
										business with the client. He continue the discussion with the
										Entrepreneurial Management topic. Introduced the business
										model canvas and value proposition canvas and how to make it.
										After the discussion, Mr. Nisperos held a group activity. Each
										group must make their own business model canvas and value
										proposition canvas and present it after.</p>

